│ THOUGHT: The transformation is still miscompiling because simplifyIVRemainder is allowed to perform numerator-based replacements for SRem, which can be unsafe in presence of negative   │
│ denominators or when ScalarEvolution makes incorrect assumptions. To make the pass conservative, I'll restrict the "replace remainder with numerator (or zero)" simplifications to only  │
│ apply to unsigned remainder (URem). This means gating the block that checks N < D and N-1 < D under !IsSigned, so SRem will not be simplified this way. This should prevent folding SRem │
│ to the numerator and avoid the incorrect ret 729259140.                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '392,405s/^  if (UsedAsNumerator) {/  if (!IsSigned && UsedAsNumerator) {/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyIndVar.cpp && submit-patch                                          │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
