│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation likely hinges on simplifying signed remainder with a potentially negative, loop-variant denominator. Even after gating transformations to numerator-only and │
│ disabling general remainder simplifications early, the pass may still incorrectly apply the "replace remainder with numerator" when ScalarEvolution can't guarantee denominator          │
│ non-negativity. To make this conservative, I will add a check to ensure the denominator is provably non-negative before performing any numerator-based remainder simplifications,        │
│ restricting them to cases where D >= 0 (and only for URem via prior gating). This should prevent folding srem incorrectly in the reproducer.                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -n '380,420p' llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyIndVar.cpp | sed 's/^  if (!IsSigned && UsedAsNumerator) {$/  if (!IsSigned && UsedAsNumerator) {\n    if                            │
│ (!SE->isKnownNonNegative(D))\n      return;/' | sed -n '1,200p' > /tmp/siv.tmp && sed -i '380,420s/^.*$//' llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyIndVar.cpp && nl -ba /tmp/siv.tmp | sed -n  │
│ '1,200p' >> llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyIndVar.cpp && submit-patch                                                                                                                 │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
